Bored with breakfast? This winter delight is a twist on your usual Weet-Bix
Share to Facebook Share to Twitter Email Print
1. Using a small saucepan, heat the berries with the apple, cinnamon and honey, reduce for a couple of minutes until thick.
2. In a shallow breakfast bowl, layer your crumble by alternating half a crushed Weet-Bix™ biscuit with a spoonful of the berry mix. Continue with layers.
3. Pour over hot milk, ensuring even coverage.
4. Finish by sprinkling toasted sliced almonds on top.
For a gluten free option use Gluten Free Weetbix.
Recipe and image kindly provided by Sanitarium Health and Wellbeing Company
